<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by shiniar on 06-28-2001 12:24 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Befallen has fallen  :(

My friend and I (both level 14) have been hunting there for the last couple days, haveing a great time on the second floor.  Then *BOOM* right after patch, the DE's invade and we can't even make it to zone before being obliterated.

The smallest mobs were blue to us (I think around lvl 12 or 13.. some went green when I hit lvl 15)  EVERYTHING aggros on EVERYTHING.. Lvl 50's showed up to investigate and were swamped with mobs at the enterence.. had to burn their way through the dungeon to explore it.  

MOB's now can be full range of casters and melee (starting on first floor).  Nothing like walking into the place and getting killed by your charmed partner before making it to the first door.  

The upsides are that spawn rate is MUCH faster then before, loot has improved dramatically, (but items of any value are no-drop), lots of gold, and low level caster items on the smaller mobs (most casters have cracked staffs and senior apprentice robes).

If you don't mind hiding in a corner, avoiding mega-train route, and avoid exploring at all costs, the exp and loot are nice.  But moving around means death.

Shintiar </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
